# Input-method selector, read by /etc/X11/Xsession.d/70im-config_launch at login.
#
# "run_im none" = start NO input-method framework. We deliberately disable IBus:
# its XIM bridge (ibus-x11 / ibus-extension-gtk3) leaks thousands of invisible 1x1
# windows over time, and once enough pile up, every GTK4 app (Nautilus,
# gnome-text-editor, ...) aborts on launch with an xcb "_XReply" assertion.
# US-English typing needs no IM framework, and Vocalinux injects text via
# xdotool/XTEST (not IBus), so nothing here depends on IBus.
#
# Revert with:  run_im ibus   (or `im-config -n ibus`)
run_im none
